    "name": "Kan Sano",
    "profile": "Keyboardist, track-maker, and producer, Kan Sano began his collegiate musical education studies of Jazz at Berklee College of Music in Boston, MA, USA, graduating in 2006.\r\n\r\nWhile being a leading figure in the beat-music scene, he enjoys the freedom of improvisations on the piano in his own unique style, which can be described as a fusion of jazz and classical music. In addition to his main instrument, the piano, Sano also adds the trumpet, bass, and drums to his musical arsenal during his live band performance sets, which bring the audience to a standing frenzy.\r\n\r\nHis released songs \"On My Way Home,\" \"DT pt. 2,\" and \"Sit At The Piano\" have each been streamed more than 10 million times on various platforms. While establishing himself specifically as a Japanese musician, he became the first Japanese Artist to release a song on the prestigious UK label, Decca Records.\r\n\r\nPreviously recognized as a member of the band HEX, Kan Sano is active in both domestic Japanese markets and internat",
